RELEASE_CHANNEL=local
RELEASE_VERSION=0.9.0-phase9

Cloudflare dry-run script:
- Validate required env vars.
- Print planned actions.
- Do not call Cloudflare API unless CLOUDFLARE_DRY_RUN=false.
- Even when false, never print token values.
- Support tunnel name, hostname, zone ID, account ID, DNS CNAME target, Zero Trust template.
- Print deployment summary.
- Explicitly say Cloudflare production automation belongs in cvsz/zeaz-platform.

Terraform:
- Provider-neutral skeleton where possible.
- Variables for app name, environment, region, domain, image tags, database sizing, Redis sizing, Cloudflare config.
- Outputs for app URL, backend URL, database endpoint, Redis endpoint, Cloudflare hostname.
- No credentials.
- README explains adaptation for AWS/GCP/local VM.

Kubernetes:
- placeholders only for secrets
- non-root containers where possible
- readiness/liveness probes
- resource requests/limits
- DRY_RUN=true by default
- PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true by default

Scripts:
release.sh:
- validate clean git tree
- run backend tests
- run frontend tests
- build Docker images
- tag release
- generate changelog summary
- print deployment checklist

deploy-dev.sh:
- docker compose up --build
- run migrations
- run smoke test

deploy-prod.sh:
- require DEPLOY_CONFIRM=yes
- require APP_ENV=production
- require production safety check pass
- build/pull images
- run migrations
- start services
- run smoke test

rollback.sh:
- require ROLLBACK_CONFIRM=yes
- roll back to previous image tag or compose backup
- run smoke test

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

cd ../frontend
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm use 20
npm test
npm run build

cd ..
docker build -f infra/docker/backend.Dockerfile .
docker build -f infra/docker/frontend.Dockerfile .
docker build -f infra/docker/nginx.Dockerfile .
docker compose config
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml config

